grabiner 
Advisory Board
Posts: 20279 Joined: Tue Feb 20, 2007 11:58 pm
Location: Columbia, MD



Re: Supplemental Annuity Collective Trust of New Jersey (SACT)


Quote


Postby grabiner » Thu Jun 23, 2016 10:09 pm 
fireman44 wrote:My fear with this SACT is I will be invested for 18 more years. ( when I retire )It is heavily invested in Stocks and I have no way for control AA.It shouldn't be your entire portfolio even if you do use it (and as I indicated above, I don't recommend the regular version).  It's fine to have your annuity portfolio in stocks if you can hold enough bonds in your Roth IRA and taxable account to get your desired allocation.In NJ, it is particularly attractive to use either NJ munis or Treasury bonds in your taxable account (depending on your tax bracket), as NJ does not tax capital gains on "qualified investment funds" which hold bonds exempt from NJ tax.
 David Grabiner


