OK, I'll bite.
I don't know anything about the SACT NJ. I thought Tony would respond as I believe he knows about SACT NJ.
Other comments:
Past performance is not important.
If you cannot get the fund choices, the asset class and the ER, there isn't much we can respond too. We need this information so we can construct a balanced diversified portfolio.
I noticed on one of your links the form is dated 1999.
Forget about the specific sponsor for a minute. What is your question? And then a discussion might ensue.











Steve Schullo
